track_notes:
Sorry, some wrong points in the wood. We took the forest road to go back. It is not that much longer but safer. It took us 10 hrs to get back to the starting point. Incl. 1 1/2 hrs for QSOs. Ca. 900m elevation one way. May be You can do it in 6 hrs when You are 59+. No water on the route!
Fantstic views. There is a bus stop but I query whether it is possible by public transport in one day. 73 de Martin, OE3VBU
